16 SUMMARY
1177 This bill establishes the electricity cost fairness credit to provide a credit of up to $600
1188 against income taxes imposed on residents and part-year residents. The credit, based on
1199 the sales tax fairness credit, is refundable, is phased out based on income and is indexed to
2200 inflation.
